#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:47
msgid "We run as a distributed, high performance team using a few principles:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:50
msgid "1) Work anywhere with good Internet"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:51
msgid ""
"Working from anywhere means more time with loved ones, no commute and "
"controlling everything about your workspace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:53
msgid ""
"The one requirement is having the ability to occassionally `join video "
"calls using Zoom <https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/201362023"
"-System-Requirements-for-PC-Mac-and-Linux>`__ between 8am and 1pm "
"California time, which requires a good enough internet connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:55
msgid ""
"Recommended download/upload speeds should be 8 Mbps/512 kbps for smooth "
"group calling and screensharing, with a bare minimum of 4 Mbps / 128 "
"kbps. The `CRS Video Conference Bandwidth Speed Tool "
"<http://speed.conferenceroomsystems.com/>`__ can be used to check your "
"internet speed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:57
msgid ""
"There are exceptions to this requirement, for example: part time roles "
"that don't need to take meetings, or roles providing support outside core"
" meeting hours."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:60
msgid "2) Be explicit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:62
msgid ""
"Working in a distributed organization means it may take time before a "
"person reads your message and responds, so make sure you are clear."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:64
msgid "Communicate relevant information in the first message:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:66
msgid ""
"Avoid \"Are you free to talk?\" and \"`Can we talk about something at "
"3pm? <https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/16/jobs/when-youre-in-charge-your-"
"whisper-may-feel-like-a-shout.html?_r=0>`__\", instead use \"Can we speak"
" about ulimit issue Customer X is having?\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:68
msgid "Write unambiguously:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:70
msgid ""
"Avoid \"I think the answer is Yes\", instead use \"Yes\", \"No\", or \"I "
"think the answer is Yes, I'll confirm with Steve and let you know.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:72
msgid ""
"Likewise, we emphasize written communication. Reading is faster than "
"listening and it reaches more people, which means more happens in less "
"time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:75
msgid "3) Follow through"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:76
msgid ""
"When working on problems, make sure to be clear about next steps, and "
"either follow through or create a ticket to track the work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:79
msgid "4) Hang out"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:80
msgid ""
"We have `warm-ups <https://docs.mattermost.com/process/training.html"
"#warm-ups>`__ in some meetings to learn more about each other. It's part "
"of a culture where we get to know each other."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:82
msgid ""
"Find time after meetings and video conferences to get to know your "
"teammates. Ask them about their weekends and how their life is outside of"
" work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:84
msgid ""
"When you meet in person at off-sites and events, build on those "
"relationships."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:87
msgid "5) Be the change you want to see"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:88
msgid ""
"When something's not clearly documented, take the initiative to figure "
"out what's going on and update the documentation for the people who come "
"after you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/working-at-mattermost.rst:90
msgid ""
"`Learn, Master, Teach <https://docs.mattermost.com/process/training.html"
"#learn-master-teach>`__ is a model we use to pass on training after "
"you've been trained to help grow everyone at the company."
msgstr ""

